						               													<description>Game based on the traditional Game of the Goose. It was used in a giant size in 1983 in the Spanish most famous TV contest &amp;quot;Un, dos, tres... responda otra vez&amp;quot; (on which the British &amp;quot;Three, two, one&amp;quot; was based) and shortly after comerciallized as a board game for the general public.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For this game two different dices are used: One is the traditional dice from 1 to 6; and in the other there are four images of Botilde, one x2 and one negative sign. If it falls in Botilde the throw of the other dice remaines unchanged; while a x2 doubles that roll; and the - forces to go back instead of advance.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As in the Game of the Goose, falling into a Botilde means going &amp;quot;from boot to boot and shoot because it touches you&amp;quot;. There are also question boxes; and trip boxes, which assignes a try-out. The other boxes all have a specific function, sometimes positive and sometimes negative, including those that make leaving the game. In the last section, called &amp;quot;the magic circle&amp;quot;, the players would go around until they are eliminated or fall exactly in the Booty playing only with the traditional dice.&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary (translated)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Juego basado en la tradicional Oca. Se utiliz&amp;oacute; en un formato gigante en 1983 en el concurso de TV &amp;quot;Un, dos, tres... responda otra vez&amp;quot;, para ser comercializado al poco tiempo como juego de mesa para el p&amp;uacute;blico general.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Para este juego se utilizaban dos dados diferentes: Uno era el dado tradicional del uno al seis; y en el otro hab&amp;iacute;a cuatro im&amp;aacute;genes de Botilde, un x2 y un -, si ca&amp;iacute;a en Botilde la tirada del otro dado quedaba sin cambios, mientras que un x2 doblaba esa tirada, y el - hac&amp;iacute;a retroceder en lugar de avanzar.  &amp;#10;Como en la oca, caer en una Botilde significaba ir &amp;quot;de bota a bota y chuta porque te toca&amp;quot;. Tambi&amp;eacute;n hab&amp;iacute;a casillas de pregunta, y casillas de tropez&amp;oacute;n, que asignaban una prueba.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;El resto de casillas ten&amp;iacute;an todas una funci&amp;oacute;n espec&amp;iacute;fica, unas veces positiva y otras negativas, incluyendo las que hac&amp;iacute;an abandonar el juego. En el &amp;uacute;ltimo tramo, llamado &amp;quot;el c&amp;iacute;rculo m&amp;aacute;gico&amp;quot;, los jugadores ir&amp;iacute;an dando vueltas hasta que fueran eliminados o cayeran exactamente en el bot&amp;iacute;n jugando solamente con el dado tradicional.&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
